          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>All hematological parameters are within normal limits except for a markedly elevated platelet distribution width (PDW), which may indicate increased variability in platelet size, possibly reflecting platelet activation or increased turnover. No evidence of anemia, leukocytosis, or thrombocytopenia. Correlate PDW finding clinically; isolated elevation may be nonspecific if other parameters and clinical context are unremarkable.</td></tr></table></div>"
